Pre-Game Insights: George Bailey has confirmed that Steve Smith won’t be included in Australia’s playing 11 against New Zealand.
Mitchell Marsh is set to be the number three of the side, whereas the emergence of Tim David in the lower middle order has cemented his place as well.
The Australian team will rely on its all-rounders yet again, and the trio of Mitch Marsh, Glenn Maxwell and Marcus Stoinis will play a vital role.
